# Mandatory Principles: TDD · DTRT · DRY · Epistemology

**Precedence:** mandatory — overrides general defaults that would skip tests, allow failing-test releases, or batch commits.

## TDD
- Write tests **before** implementation; observe new tests **fail** before writing production code.
- Red → Green → **Refactor** (mandatory step). Full workflow: [strict-tdd-definition.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/strict-tdd-definition.mdc).
- Red ends when tests **compile and fail** (stubs allowed so they compile).
- All tests must pass before any release. Details in `MANDATORY_TESTING_RULES.md` Rule 1.

## DTRT
- Proper solutions, not quick fixes. Follow established patterns. Consider long-term implications.

## DRY
- Extract common functionality; refactor when patterns emerge.

## Epistemology
- Distinguish verified facts from hypotheses ([epistemology.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/epistemology.mdc)).

## Release quality gate
- **No release (any kind) without a green test suite.** The release script (`Development/scripts/release-process.sh`) runs macOS + iOS tests — the agent does not run the full suite before release; the script does.

## Git hygiene
- Commit cadence is **one edit = one commit** per [commit-after-every-edit.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commit-after-every-edit.mdc) (with the project.yml + XcodeGen exception).
- **Commit before every test run** — see [commit-before-test.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commit-before-test.mdc). Do not invoke any test command while `git status` is dirty.
- Commit message practices per `.cursorrules` (clear what/why, issue links, imperative mood).
